Out of the box 2002 Shiny Charizard Combat Figure by Hasbro✨🔥 Don’t worry this didn’t come from my sealed box this was found at a friend’s table in at Denver @collect_a_con last year and we did a trade cause I just had to have it cause it was complete and it worked! Toys are meant to be played with right? 

The Shiny Pokémon Combat Figure line by Hasbro is the only American toy line to have made Shiny Pokémon toys! Finding loose complete toys of this line is tough and can be pricey but completing the entire 10 Shiny Pokémon Combat Figure line is beyond difficult and very expensive. To give you an idea, it took me 3 years and close to $10,000 to get it done! I believe that I’m the first to have completed it as well! 

Thanks to @baeybuy for the trade!

2012 Shiny Unova Starters these Bandai Kids are also Daisuki lottery prizes! Yes these were awarded through the same Daisuki Club that the Master Scroll Trophy card has come from. Only 1000 were given out as prizes and these rank high on the list of rare figures in Pokémon! The box that you see is what these came in, as you can see there’s nothing special about the packaging because these were never sale! Sure the shiny colors are very subtle but these are very cool to have and own!

Shiny Pokémon and the heavily grown interest behind catching them has drastically increased with the Pokémon games as well as Pokémon Go!

2002 BGS 9 Digimon Digi-Battle Series 6 HiAndromon🤖 

Population: 2 and none graded higher

Digimon Digi-Battle is quite honestly interesting when you take a look at it! Series 1 and 2 were printed to oblivion by Upper Deck and Series 3-6 were done by Bandai and were extremely short printed. Series 1 and 2 came out in booster boxes whereas Series 3-6 came out in blister packs. Finding Series 3-6 sealed product is also extremely hard to find and if you do then you better prepared to cough up a pretty penny. Just to give an idea, there were no images of Series 6 for over 20 years until pictures started to surface! One Series 6 Blister pack has sold at $5,900! With such scarcity of product and very little mint condition ungraded holos the population reports won’t see much movement. Most of the population reports for cards in high grades are less than 10 which is insane! Digimon has always been an anime I love and enjoy and I notice the passion in other members of this growing community if you haven’t given the new Digimon TCG a try definitely do so and I highly recommend for each of you to watch the anime cause it’s so good!

Pokémon’s 20th Anniversary in 2016 brought out some of the most iconic Japanese Promos we know today. Most of us in the hobby recall the boxes to the Mario & Luigi Pikachu being super cheap and passing it up because other opportunities popped up. For me I remember the boxes were $300 a pop when I first got into the hobby and since then these cards and the boxes have only gone up in value! The Mario and Pokémon collaboration itself is beyond iconic and it makes me wonder if we will ever see something like this during the 30th anniversary like Zelda and Pokémon or Kirby and Pokémon!

This is a PSA 10 Luigi Pikachu I graded for @crystalxtcg a few years ago and it’s still a card that I hope to add to the PC one day!

2002 PSA 9 1st Edition Shining Mewtwo from Neo Destiny🤌🏾

With a current market value of approximately $1,300 this card 2 years ago would’ve sold at approximately $2,700 during the card boom of 2020-2021! Sure that’s a little over a 50% decline but if you go back to 2019 this card in a PSA 9 was selling for approximately $460! It’s important to understand that markets are cyclical and it’s important to use your gut when make sound purchases! From my perspective Shining Pokémon cards from the Neo era will always do well due to its iconic nature and with passion and resurgence behind shiny collecting Pokémon this would be a beautiful add to the collection. 

This beautiful card has come fresh in for consignment! If you or anyone you know is interested in selling their collection or pieces shoot me a DM! If you are looking for someone to middleman sales, sourcing of product and trades reach out!

Struck Gold 🏆 2000 CGC Pristine 10 Pichu & Friends Famitsu Magazine Phone Card! For those of y’all who don’t know, I sold a copy of this card in a BGS 9.5 back in December 2021 and after selling it I regretted it immensely. I searched and searched until a good friend @crystaltcgx sold a ungraded copy to me last year! Fast forward to this week at the @nsccshow I graded it with @cgccards and now I have the most clean copy of the Pichu & Friends card in the world! 

The card features that classic 3D art from Pokémon Stadium with Johto Pokémon!

Thankful for the people in this hobby that constantly help me grow as a person, a creator, and a hobbyist!

While out in Japan I had to snag these Yu-Gi-Oh! Chibi style cards at 7-11! @calebxswag had told @100charizards and I to be on the look out for these cards at 7-11s because the only way you could get them was buy three Hi-Chew products for one card from the set so Andy and I went to 30+ 7-11s to complete the set. Dark Magician was the one card we found impossible to find and that’s after hitting every 7-11 we saw in Yokohama, Akihabara, Osaka, Shibuya, Shinjuku, and Tokyo! These mini adventures we took in Japan was a massive highlight of mine

CGC 9 Pokémon the Movie 2000 Topps 1st Appearance Lugia🌊 Between CGC, PSA, & BGS the population for this immensely rare Pokémon card is 9 with 0 10s. It is so crazy to finally cross this off my list of cards to have in my PC and it was a journey to upgrade my BGS 8 to this monster of a card 

@dzagamer & I dubbed this card the “Ghost Rare Lugia” 3 years ago after Yu-Gi-Oh!’s ghost rare cards and it just took off in popularity. This card is Lugia’s rookie card, is older than WOTC’s 1st Edition Neo Genesis Lugia and far more difficult to grade. 

With @poke_mik BGS 9 selling for a little over $25,000 on @pwccmarketplace it’s just crazy to me to see that this card finally has the recognition it deserves

Could the D23 Elsa eventually become just as iconic as the 1st Edition Base Charizard or the 1st Edition LOB Blue-Eyes White Dragon or an Alpha Black Lotus? Who knows! What I do know is that it has brought in more people into the hobby and that it makes me hopeful!
